about: I don't read books, I eat them. There was once a time when I didn't note titles or authors, just opened books and started reading. Even now I rarely see the title page of a book. You'll rarely find me without a backpack full of reading material -books, magazines, flyers. I've been this way my whole life.

name: Erica
about:
Right now I'm using this more as a database of books I want to read so when the moment arrives when I'm thinking 'now what's that book I was thinking of?' I will be able to look it up!

Also, my friend challenged me to list all the books I've read. When I started adding silly stuff like children's books, I felt like I was really scraping the bottom of the barrel. That's okay, I guess.

I'm really bad at starting new books before I've finished the one I'm reading...as you can see on my list. Perhaps that'll be a new year's resolution...because I'm so good at keeping those.
